channel.description: I'm using a Fr33sc4p3 Pkz source to make a server, and I'm following this guide: [url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,134771.0.html]http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,134771.0.html[/url] I cant seem to port forward correctly. [center][size=30pt]STOP!!![/size][/center] I have been to portforward.com! Don't even suggest that. It doesn't have my router, which is an RCA DCM425. I need to port-forward with that router, however, when I put it's default gate 74.138.208.1 in the address bar, it says "Page cannot be displayed". I have tryed 74.138.208.2 etc. In the past, on a different computer, I ended up using a port forwading software that I had to get a crack for. Someone please help! Thanks
